  "text": "To understand the nature of this limitation, it is of interest to compare the features we have found in the mouse with those previously described in Xenopus oocytes and eggs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . At the very beginning of oocyte growth, diplotene Xenopus oocytes display a significant level of NHEJ and no apparent SSA activities. With further oocyte growth, however, NHEJ rapidly becomes undetectable, while an SSA activity appears and progressively increases, by eventually maximizing at the end of oogenesis. During oocyte matu- a Number of p900SB2-derived A ϩ B fragment pairs injected/GV or pronucleus. b Absolute numbers of recombinant pSB2 copies were estimated by the dose-response curves of Fig. 2C (oocytes) and Fig. 4A (embryos) . Values indicate mean Ϯ SEM.",
